      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:7:3:1",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو الْحَسَنِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنَّ شُرْبَ الْمَاءِ الْبَارِدِ أَكْثَرُ تَلَذُّذاً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Al Hakam who said, ",
          "‘Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Drinking the cold water is abundant enjoyment’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn al-Hakam who has said the following: “Abu al-Hassan, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Drinking cold water is more delicious.’” "
        ]
      }
